root_cause_details:
Problem: User unable to authorise OBA consent in iOS application

Why: On 13 Sept 2024 this PR merged by @Mohammad Saadat to increase the app modularisation that impac this flow

Why: In the OpenBankingShowConsentRouter, the showSecondFactorFlow function was responsible for displaying the 2fa pop-up

    private func showSecondFactorFlow(
        for error: ReauthenticationError,
        failureHandler: @escaping (Error) -> Void
    ) {
        guard let navigationController else {
            failureHandler(error)
            return
        }
        globalActivity.hide()
        launchAuthenticationModuleFlow(
            destination: .reauthenticationIfNeeded(
                error: error,
                onNonReauthenticationError: { error in failureHandler(error) },
                completion: {
                    if let error = $0.error { failureHandler(error) }
                }
            ),
            navigationController: navigationController,
            dependencyContainer: AuthenticationDependenciesContainer()
        )
      }
Why: The navigationController is a computed property that should handle showing the 2fa in the in the OpenBankingShowConsentRouter



private var navigationController: UINavigationController? {
    rootNavigationController?.presentedViewController as? UINavigationController
}
Why: in this PR, to show the account consent flow, the below code is implemented



launchBusinessOpenBankingFlow(
    destination: .accountsConsentAuthorization(
      consent: consent,
      completion: complete
    ),
  tabsController: controller,
  navigationController: navigationController
)
Why: the same navigationController is used to passed to the new module to handle the 2fa pop-up but the difference is the navigationController does not exist at the moment the flow is started, because navigationController does not exist at the moment the flow is started it never showes the 2fa pop-up 



Problem: on 11 Oct 2024 supporting the force update pop-up is merged by @Rinat Aynulin in this PR to show force update pop up for version 6.66, 6.66.1, 6.67, but the Force update pop-up automatically closes in theses versions

Why: The force update pop-up closes automatically when it should remain open
Why: StatusViewModel.error was used to create a StatusViewModel

Why: The autoDismissal property in the StatusViewModel was set to nil

Why: Setting autoDismissal to nil unintentionally led to the automatic closure of the force update pop-up

Why: Setting autoDismissal to nil in StatusViewModel caused the force update pop-up to close automaticallyIs this a re-occurring incident?
